Windows powers most desktops. Here's a guide to versions, features, tools, and moreâ€”from Home to Enterprise.

Windows Versions & Editions:
Windows 10/11: Released 2015/2021; ongoing updates. Editions: Home (retail, Defender, Cortana), Pro (RDP, BitLocker, domains), Pro for Workstations (up to 6TB RAM, ReFS), Enterprise (AppLocker, BranchCache).
Upgrade Paths: In-place (keeps apps/settings) or clean install. From Win7/8.1 to 10; 10 to 11. No x86 to x64 direct upgrades.

Key Features:
Domain Services: Active Directory for centralized management.
Workgroups/Domains: Peer groups vs. enterprise auth.
RDP: Remote Desktop (Pro/Enterprise only).
BitLocker/EFS: Full disk/file encryption.
Group Policy: Local (gpedit.msc) or domain management.

Command Line Tools:
File Mgmt: dir, cd, copy, xcopy, robocopy.
System: hostname, format, sfc (scan files), chkdsk, diskpart.
Network: ipconfig, ping, netstat, nslookup, tracert, pathping, net.
Other: shutdown, gpupdate, winver.

Management Tools:
Task Manager: Processes, performance, services, startup.
MMC: Event Viewer, Disk Mgmt, Task Scheduler, Device Mgr, Perf Monitor, Group Policy.
Additional: System Info, Resource Monitor, msconfig, Disk Cleanup, defrag, regedit.

Control Panel & Settings:
Control Panel: Internet Options, Devices/Printers, Programs/Features, Network/Sharing, System, Firewall, Sound, User Accounts, Power Options.
Settings: Time/Language, Update/Security, Personalization, Apps, Privacy, System, Devices, Network/Internet, Gaming, Accounts.

Network Technologies:
Shared Resources: Folders/printers; map drives (net use).
Firewall: Defender Firewall; exceptions, rules.
IP Config: DHCP (auto), APIPA (169.254.x.x), static.
Connections: Wired/wireless/WWAN; VPN; metered networks.

Installing Applications:
Requirements: 32/64-bit, graphics (integrated/dedicated), RAM, CPU, storage.
Methods: Downloadable, physical media, ISO mounts.
Considerations: Impact on device/network/operations; use trusted sources.
